pros:
fast pace;
vasetile product familiies
near city center;

cons:
I think a few existing reviews on right on. 

- They give you good title and good pay to attract you, but once you jon, they treat you like  consultant not employee;

- HQ is in China, people there treat you like outsiders not peers. No respect, all they want is to squeeze your brain juice;

- Management is horrible. 
  * They want you to propose the direction/plan and to get money on your own from HQ; 
  * They also want you to make money in a few month, otherwise, your days are numbered!
  * They have no direction nor long term goals,  and can cut off your project at any given time;

- There is no stock option or ESPP, but Chinese employees all gets good stocks and bonus;

You either leave the company or they lay you off around one year.

pros:
- quite fair appraisal system ;
- good compensation & benefits package (yearly salary increase, monthy / yearly awards, overtime payment, transportation allowance);
- friendly working envirnoment and helpful staff (of course, this also depends on the team and people you are working with).

cons:
- constant change of work responsabilities and tasks / no clear direction or strategy, not even for medium term ;
- a rules / process based working process / very little opportunities to change anything ;
- communication with chineese staff is often full of difficulties and misunderstandings (even top management chineese staff does not handle english language or any other language except chineese, very well);
- internal mobility is lacking and not encouraged / you may end up locked in the same department/position for multiple years;
- lack of promotion opportunities (except for the case when a more senior staff leaves the company or goes into maternal leave).

